{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-tsx","path":"/start-learning-dev","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"ilyagru","author":"Ilya Gruzhevski","siteUrl":"https://ilyagru.github.io"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"6188bad5-384d-59ad-8475-86db1ad62351","excerpt":"Some people ask me how to start doing some things in the programming world. So I decided to post some kind of answer with a few ideas to get you started. This is not the complete guide to programming. What we have First of all, take a look at what you have, what you want to do, and why you want to…","html":"<p>Some people ask me how to start doing some things in the programming world. So I decided to post some kind of answer with a few ideas to get you started. This is not the complete guide to programming.</p>\n<h2>What we have</h2>\n<p>First of all, take a look at what you have, what you want to do, and why you want to be a programmer.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 650px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/d5343eaa84f637f1730181196a17d4b2/9d8cf/searching.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 61.34969325153374%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Searching\"\n        title=\"Searching\"\n        src=\"/static/d5343eaa84f637f1730181196a17d4b2/663f3/searching.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/d5343eaa84f637f1730181196a17d4b2/5e043/searching.png 163w,\n/static/d5343eaa84f637f1730181196a17d4b2/e5cc6/searching.png 325w,\n/static/d5343eaa84f637f1730181196a17d4b2/663f3/searching.png 650w,\n/static/d5343eaa84f637f1730181196a17d4b2/d880f/searching.png 975w,\n/static/d5343eaa84f637f1730181196a17d4b2/9d8cf/searching.png 1216w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h3>Maybe iOS?</h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>“Everybody in this country should learn to program a computer, because it teaches you how to think” — Steve Jobs</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>For example, if you have a MacBook, I would advise you to try iOS apps. <a href=\"https://swift.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Swift</a> is wonderful to go here but you need some knowledge of Objected Oriented Programming principles, compilators, etc. But it’s possible to learn it if you want. As I wrote in my <a href=\"/remame-story\">previous post</a> you can start with the books from Apple. They are very cool for the beginning and could give you more motivation. Then you can find others.</p>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/book/the-swift-programming-language-swift-4-2/id881256329\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">The Swift Programming Language</a> by Apple</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/book/intro-to-app-development-with-swift/id1118575552\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Intro to App Development with Swift</a> by Apple</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/book/app-development-with-swift/id1219117996\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">App Development with Swift</a> by Apple</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Pro-Swift-4-1-Paul-Hudson/dp/1985779781\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">PRO SWIFT</a> by Paul Hudson</li>\n</ol>\n<p>You can find a lot of courses on different websites. One of the most outstanding could be a Stanford course <a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/pl/course/developing-ios-11-apps-with-swift/id1309275316\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Developing iOS 11 Apps with Swift</a>. One of the coolest seems <a href=\"https://designcode.io\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Design+Code</a>. Also there is a cool growth path for an iOS developer that I found and finished completely. It’s just a recommendation but it covers a lot of things which every Apple developer should know. Available as a <a href=\"https://trello.com/b/dOV9dvBu/a-path-to-mastery-for-ios-development\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Trello board</a>, so you can grab and copy it to your own board and complete challenges one after another. A bunch of cool tutorials are here on the <a href=\"https://www.raywenderlich.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Ray Wenderlich website</a>.</p>\n<p>One of the best solutions here could be implementing your own idea if you have one. It could be either a simple Todo list or something more complex. Even a mobile game but it could be difficult and you can get desperate. So do not rush!</p>\n<h3>Maybe Frontend / Web?</h3>\n<p>If there is no Mac (or there is), then the Web development (at least creating simple websites), because it’s very extensive and, in my opinion, there are more chances to specifically decide on further study. It is easy to start doing something and see the result almost at the same time. But it’s not difficult to get lost and lose motivation. In this case, you need not to give up, it will pass when you know more.</p>\n<p>For the web, I would advise to start as soon as possible with practice, while reading books in parallel and studying terminology. In fact, learn <a href=\"https://www.w3schools.com/html/html_intro.asp\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">HTML</a> and <a href=\"https://www.w3schools.com/html/html_css.asp\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">CSS</a>. This is not really programming, but you can add <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">JavaScript</a>. On the Internet, there are still many articles with a path you could take to become a JavaScript ninja or guru.</p>\n<p>As for JavaScript, programming begins with it. If you don’t want to go all the way into site building, then you can go straight to JavaScript, in which case it would be better to use the Node.js ecosystem. On the Internet, there is a lot about it. Personally, for me online courses weren’t so effective. It was more useful just to find different designs on the Internet, for example on <a href=\"https://dribbble.com/search?q=landing+page\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Dribbble</a>, and try to implement them just looking. Increase the difficulty as you develop. Anyway, you could try these platforms.</p>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.khanacademy.org/computing/computer-programming\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Khanacademy</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.codecademy.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Cocecademy</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://htmlacademy.ru\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Html Academy [RU]</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://learn.shayhowe.com/html-css/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Learn to Code HTML &#x26; CSS</a></li>\n</ol>\n<p>For references</p>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"https://htmlreference.io/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">HTML</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://cssreference.io\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">CSS</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://javascript.info\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">JavaScript</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.w3schools.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">W3C</a> — This resource is quite fundamental, because in general, W3C is an organization that develops HTML and CSS standards.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>There are a lot of guys who make videos. You just need to google it and choose your favorite. On English YouTube I would highly recommend this channel <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/thenetninja\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">The Net Ninja</a>. He explains very clearly in spoken English. On Russian YouTube, <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/artsorax\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Sorax</a>.</p>\n<p>The fundamentals can be found anywhere, just the basics are not a problem to find, the problems will begin when you want to go deep, because the quality and quantity of more advanced material is much lower. Then of course you can try single page applications, <a href=\"https://reactjs.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">React.js</a>, <a href=\"https://vuejs.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Vue.js</a> and <a href=\"https://2018.stateofjs.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">the family</a>.</p>\n<p>For more JS and server-side JS you can take a look at these resources.</p>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/vasanthk/js-bits\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">JS-bits</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/workshopper/learnyounode\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Learn You Node</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://nodeschool.io\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Nodeschool</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://javascript30.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">JavaScript 30 Days Challenge</a> — Here you can find other courses from <a href=\"https://wesbos.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Wes Bos</a></li>\n</ol>\n<p>As for Frontend books, I can advise these. Just look if there is a newer edition.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.learningwebdesign.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Learning Web Design</a> by Jennifer Robbins</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"http://shop.oreilly.com/product/0636920024996\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">CSS3 Big Book 3rd Edition</a> by David McFarland</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1118907442/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Web Design with HTML, CSS, JavaScript and jQuery Set</a> by Jon Duckett</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/CSS-Secrets-Lea-Verou/dp/1449372635\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">CSS Secrets</a> by Lea Verou</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://html5forwebdesigners.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">HTML5 For Web Designers</a> by Jeremy Keith</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://abookapart.com/products/css3-for-web-designers\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">CSS3 For Web Designers</a> by Dan Cederholm</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://abookapart.com/products/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">A Book Apart library</a> in total has many good books</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://learning.oreilly.com/library/view/head-first-javascript/9781449340124/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Head First JavaScript Programming</a> by Elisabeth Robson, Eric T. Freeman</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/JavaScript-Good-Parts-Douglas-Crockford/dp/0596517742\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">JavaScript: The Good Parts</a> by Douglas Crockford</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"http://shop.oreilly.com/product/0636920032977\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Web Development with Node and Express</a> by Todd Brown</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://legacy.gitbook.com/book/frontendmasters/front-end-developer-handbook-2018/details\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Front-end Developer Handbook 2018</a> by Frontend Masters</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"http://it-ebooks.info\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">More books</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Even <a href=\"https://jsbooks.revolunet.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">more books</a></p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Anything else?</h3>\n<p>You can try any other programming language, such as <a href=\"https://www.python.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Python</a> or <a href=\"https://www.ruby-lang.org/en/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Ruby</a>. They are mainly used for backend stuff. <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/index.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Java</a> and <a href=\"https://kotlinlang.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Kotlin</a> are needed for Android. Maybe some modern languages like <a href=\"https://golang.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Go</a>, <a href=\"https://www.r-project.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">R</a>, or <a href=\"https://www.rust-lang.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Rust</a>. I would not recommend touching the languages ​​of the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C_(programming_language)\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">C</a>, <a href=\"http://www.cplusplus.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">C++</a> family for a newcomer at all. There are a lot to choose from.</p>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"https://spectrum.ieee.org/static/interactive-the-top-programming-languages-2018\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">The TOP programming languages 2018</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.codementor.io/codementorteam/beginner-programming-language-job-salary-community-7s26wmbm6\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">What Programming Language Should a Beginner Learn in 2019</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.computerscience.org/resources/computer-programming-languages/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">What are Computer Programming Languages</a></li>\n</ol>\n<p>It’s difficult to say here more because I don’t have a lot of experience with other programming languages. Just try if it sounds interesting to you! There are a lot of articles and helping tools like <a href=\"http://www.bestprogramminglanguagefor.me/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">bestprogramminglanguagefor.me</a> throughout the Internet. These picture could also suggest a correct decision.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 650px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ca12d60f22feac5b8a9a14f6d4141d7e/f97d7/programming-infographics.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 110.42944785276075%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Programming languages\"\n        title=\"Programming languages\"\n        src=\"/static/ca12d60f22feac5b8a9a14f6d4141d7e/663f3/programming-infographics.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/ca12d60f22feac5b8a9a14f6d4141d7e/5e043/programming-infographics.png 163w,\n/static/ca12d60f22feac5b8a9a14f6d4141d7e/e5cc6/programming-infographics.png 325w,\n/static/ca12d60f22feac5b8a9a14f6d4141d7e/663f3/programming-infographics.png 650w,\n/static/ca12d60f22feac5b8a9a14f6d4141d7e/d880f/programming-infographics.png 975w,\n/static/ca12d60f22feac5b8a9a14f6d4141d7e/4c573/programming-infographics.png 1300w,\n/static/ca12d60f22feac5b8a9a14f6d4141d7e/f97d7/programming-infographics.png 2000w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 650px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/c096240ca11d639f02c03cc2c120b34e/babe5/choosing-programming-language-flowchart.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 57.05521472392638%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Programming languages\"\n        title=\"Programming languages\"\n        src=\"/static/c096240ca11d639f02c03cc2c120b34e/663f3/choosing-programming-language-flowchart.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/c096240ca11d639f02c03cc2c120b34e/5e043/choosing-programming-language-flowchart.png 163w,\n/static/c096240ca11d639f02c03cc2c120b34e/e5cc6/choosing-programming-language-flowchart.png 325w,\n/static/c096240ca11d639f02c03cc2c120b34e/663f3/choosing-programming-language-flowchart.png 650w,\n/static/c096240ca11d639f02c03cc2c120b34e/d880f/choosing-programming-language-flowchart.png 975w,\n/static/c096240ca11d639f02c03cc2c120b34e/4c573/choosing-programming-language-flowchart.png 1300w,\n/static/c096240ca11d639f02c03cc2c120b34e/babe5/choosing-programming-language-flowchart.png 1379w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 650px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/27b2c54ed03aac1bd87ec61eac5d38c3/42cbc/programming-language-decision-tree.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 55.828220858895705%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Programming languages\"\n        title=\"Programming languages\"\n        src=\"/static/27b2c54ed03aac1bd87ec61eac5d38c3/663f3/programming-language-decision-tree.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/27b2c54ed03aac1bd87ec61eac5d38c3/5e043/programming-language-decision-tree.png 163w,\n/static/27b2c54ed03aac1bd87ec61eac5d38c3/e5cc6/programming-language-decision-tree.png 325w,\n/static/27b2c54ed03aac1bd87ec61eac5d38c3/663f3/programming-language-decision-tree.png 650w,\n/static/27b2c54ed03aac1bd87ec61eac5d38c3/d880f/programming-language-decision-tree.png 975w,\n/static/27b2c54ed03aac1bd87ec61eac5d38c3/4c573/programming-language-decision-tree.png 1300w,\n/static/27b2c54ed03aac1bd87ec61eac5d38c3/42cbc/programming-language-decision-tree.png 1600w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h3>Design</h3>\n<p>It would be mega useful for a developer to learn at least some basics of Design, in fact UI and UX. With this skill you could be even more effective and think more logically. A few useful resources and books to check out.</p>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.evernote.design\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">All in One Bookmark Links for Designer</a> by Evernote</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.uxpin.com/studio/ebooks/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Ebooks</a> by UXPin inc.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Principles-Beautiful-Web-Design-Designing-ebook/dp/B00TJ6UYZC\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">The Principles of Beautiful Web Design</a> by Jason Beaird, James George</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Dont-Make-Me-Think-Usability/dp/0321344758\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Don’t Make Me Think</a> by Steve Krug</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>English</h3>\n<p>Do not forget about your English. Of course if you’re reading this there is no problem but I also would advise tightening up your English if there are any doubts about this. The main language of any programming is English. Only the laziest one isn’t able to find anything here.</p>\n<h2>Last words</h2>\n<p>I tried to help objectively — I hope I helped with something. Of course this list of resources could be much longer. The point is to understand which direction to go and what works best for you. For me, for example, the so-popular <a href=\"https://www.udemy.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Udemy</a>, <a href=\"https://eu.udacity.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Udacity</a>, or <a href=\"https://www.coursera.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Coursera</a> do not work. It’s necessary to try little by little and understand what is interesting and beneficial and what is not. For motivation, it is important to have some kind of achievable goal, for example, to translate your sore idea into an application, start a startup or get a high-paying job and have goals in the course of training, such as reading 50 books, 20 pages, etc. It is really important to have self-discipline and develop a habit of doing something every day, at least a small part. I like habit-forming apps like these. But they should be just an addition to the main learning resource. There are a lot of variations with various languages for all the platforms.</p>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.enki.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Enki</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://getmimo.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Mimo</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://tapcoding.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">TapCoding</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/encode-learn-to-code/id1198851756\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Encode</a></li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.duolingo.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Duolingo</a> and <a href=\"https://lingvist.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Lingvist</a> for natural languages, <a href=\"https://vanido.io\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Vanido</a> for singing, etc. And do not be afraid to ask for help from the more experienced developers, many are responsible and can help with anything. <strong>Good luck!</strong></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Some ideas where to start programming","date":"February 07, 2019","summary":"Some people ask me how to start doing some things in the programming world. So I decided to post some kind of answer with a few ideas to get you started. This is not the complete guide to programming.","featuredImage":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"fixed","backgroundColor":"#c89848","images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/93c626288809ce404a6ffac1db8ecae9/b5380/start-learning-dev-featured-image.png","srcSet":"/static/93c626288809ce404a6ffac1db8ecae9/b5380/start-learning-dev-featured-image.png 1200w","sizes":"1200px"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/93c626288809ce404a6ffac1db8ecae9/81547/start-learning-dev-featured-image.webp 1200w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"1200px"}]},"width":1200,"height":630}}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"start-learning-dev","source":"blog","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"AUTOmation","source":"blog"},"frontmatter":{"title":"When automation becomes AUTOmation"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"remame-story","source":"blog"},"frontmatter":{"title":"How I built my first iOS app & got to TOP-25 of the Belarusian App Store"}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3128451518","4268320825","637957696"]}